  "narrative": {
    "text": "United States is a North America country with a DB-type pension system centred on the Old-Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance (Social Security OASDI). The system includes 2 schemes: Old-Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance (Social Security OASDI), Supplemental Security Income (SSI) \u2013 Means-Tested. The normal retirement age is 67 for both men and women. Contributions total 12.4% of insurable earnings (6.2% employee, 6.2% employer).",
